---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import MailtoLink from '../../components/MailtoLink.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy — Smart Control"
  description="Privacy policy for the Smart Control SRL website — how we collect, use and protect personal data."
>
  <div class="container privacy-content">
    <article>
      <p class="translation-notice" role="note">
        This is a courtesy translation. The{' '}
        <a href="/confidentialitate" class="notice-link">Romanian version</a>{' '}
        prevails in all cases.
      </p>

      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>

      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <p class="toc-title">Contents</p>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#information-collected">What information we collect and how we use it</a></li>
          <li><a href="#minors">Personal data of minors under 16</a></li>
          <li><a href="#information-transferred">Information we transfer</a></li>
          <li><a href="#links">Links to other websites</a></li>
          <li><a href="#security">Security</a></li>
          <li><a href="#rights">Your rights regarding personal data</a></li>
          <li><a href="#updates">Updates to the privacy policy</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <p>
        This policy (“Privacy policy”) describes the practices regarding the personal data we collect
        through the Site, which is hosted and operated from Romania.
      </p>

      <p>
        The privacy policy describes the types of personal data we collect, how we may use that data,
        and to whom we may transfer it.
      </p>

      <p>
        The privacy policy also presents the measures we take to protect data security. We also explain
        how you can contact us to:
      </p>

      <ol type="a">
        <li>access, rectify or delete the data you have provided to us;</li>
        <li>
          withdraw any consent you have given us for the processing of personal data;
        </li>
        <li>ask us to stop sending you information about our activity;</li>
        <li>answer any questions you have about our online privacy practices.</li>
      </ol>

      <p>
        We encourage you to read this Policy before using our Site. By using this Site, you agree to
        the terms and conditions of this Policy.
      </p>

      <h2 id="information-collected">What information we collect and how we use it</h2>

      <p>When using this Site you may provide us with the following personal data:</p>

      <h3>When contacting us by e-mail</h3>

      <p>The personal data we collect in this context are:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Last name</li>
        <li>First name</li>
        <li>E-mail address</li>
        <li>Any other personal data you choose to send us</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        We use this data to allow you to submit various requests to us, whether in relation to our
        activity or in relation to the exercise of your rights regarding personal data collected and
        processed through the Site.
      </p>

      <p>
        Information about your rights regarding personal data collected and processed through the Site
        and how to exercise them can be found in the corresponding section of this privacy policy.
      </p>

      <h2 id="minors">Personal data of minors under 16</h2>

      <p>
        Minors under the age of 16 should not submit any personal data on the website without the
        permission (consent or approval) of their legal guardian.
      </p>

      <p>
        Our Site will never knowingly collect personal data from individuals it knows to be minors
        (under 16), nor use or disclose it to any unauthorized third party without the express consent
        of the legal guardian.
      </p>

      <p>
        Taking into account the technology available in such situations, we will make reasonable
        efforts to verify whether the person holding parental responsibility for the child has given or
        approved consent, and whether the personal data is being submitted by a minor under 16.
      </p>

      <h2 id="information-transferred">Information we transfer</h2>

      <p>
        We will not transfer your personal data to third parties, with the following exceptions:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>With your consent;</li>
        <li>
          Where it is necessary to transfer information in order to provide the products and services
          you have requested;
        </li>
        <li>
          Where the information is required by the institution's partners in order to improve or
          facilitate services or products you have requested. Our partners are entitled to use the
          personal data provided only to the extent necessary for the performance of the service you
          have requested;
        </li>
        <li>
          We may transfer personal data to public authorities or institutions in accordance with legal
          provisions or in good faith if:
          <ol type="a">
            <li>it is required by a legal provision;</li>
            <li>it prevents a crime or protects national security;</li>
            <li>it protects the safety of an individual or public safety;</li>
            <li>
              the information is necessary to resolve various legal matters — for example, where your
              activities are contrary to the terms and conditions established by our institution, or to
              the instructions for using certain products and services.
            </li>
          </ol>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="links">Links to other websites</h2>

      <p>
        Please note that when you use a link to navigate from our Site to another website, this
        privacy policy no longer applies. The browsing and interaction you carry out on another
        website, including any website that links to this Site, are governed by the rules and policies
        of that website. We encourage you to read the rules and policies of the websites you visit in
        order to understand their procedures for collecting, using and disclosing personal data.
      </p>

      <h2 id="security">Security</h2>

      <p>
        The security of personal data is important to us. We maintain appropriate administrative,
        technical and physical precautions to protect personal data against accidental or unlawful
        destruction, accidental loss, alteration, disclosure or unauthorized access, use, and all
        other lawful forms of personal data processing in our possession.
      </p>

      <h2 id="rights">Your rights regarding personal data</h2>

      <p>
        In accordance with the provisions of EU Regulation no. 679/2016 (GDPR), registered
        individuals, as data subjects, have the following rights:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>the right to information;</li>
        <li>the right of access;</li>
        <li>the right to rectification;</li>
        <li>the right to object;</li>
        <li>the right to erasure (the right to be forgotten);</li>
        <li>the right to restriction of processing;</li>
        <li>the right to data portability;</li>
        <li>the right not to be subject to an individual automated decision;</li>
        <li>
          the right to lodge a complaint with the <a href="https://www.dataprotection.ro" rel="noopener" target="_blank" class="ext-link">ANSPDCP<svg class="ext-icon" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15 3h6v6"></path><path d="M10 14 21 3"></path><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"></path></svg><span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a> — the Romanian Supervisory Authority for
          Personal Data Processing.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        You may exercise any of these rights by submitting your request by e-mail to{' '}
        <MailtoLink variant="link" subject="Exercise of GDPR rights" />
        .
      </p>

      <h2 id="updates">Updates to the privacy policy</h2>

      <p>
        Our institution reserves the right to change, modify or update the privacy policy at any time,
        but will not reduce the level of protection it provides.
      </p>

      <p>
        We attach the greatest importance to privacy matters and intend to remain fully compliant with
        applicable legal requirements regarding privacy policy and the protection of personal data. We
        will periodically update the privacy policy and post any changes on this page.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-content {
    padding-block: clamp(3.5rem, 7vw, 5.5rem) clamp(3.5rem, 7vw, 5rem);
    max-width: 780px;
  }

  .translation-notice {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-cool);
    background: var(--color-blue-wash);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-bright);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin-block-end: 2rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .notice-link {
    color: var(--color-royal);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .notice-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-navy);
  }

  .toc {
    background: var(--color-blue-wash);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-blue);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin-block: 0 2.5rem;
  }

  .toc-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono, ui-monospace, monospace);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-cool);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .toc ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-inline-start: 1.25rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .toc li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    margin-block-end: 0;
  }

  .toc a {
    color: var(--color-royal);
    text-decoration: none;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .toc a:hover {
    color: var(--color-navy);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-bright);
  }

  article h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    margin-block-end: 1.75rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  article h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.125rem, 2.5vw, 1.375rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    margin-block-start: 3rem;
    margin-block-end: 1rem;
    padding-block-end: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border-blue);
    line-height: 1.3;
    scroll-margin-top: 6rem;
  }

  article h3 {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    margin-block-start: 1.5rem;
    margin-block-end: 0.5rem;
  }

  article p,
  article li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-slate);
  }

  article p {
    margin-block-end: 1rem;
  }

  article ul,
  article ol {
    margin-block: 0.5rem 1rem;
    padding-inline-start: 1.5rem;
  }

  article li {
    margin-block-end: 0.4rem;
  }

  article li > ol {
    margin-block-start: 0.4rem;
  }

  .ext-link {
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .ext-icon {
    display: inline-block;
    vertical-align: -1px;
    margin-inline-start: 0.2em;
    color: var(--color-royal);
  }

  .sr-only {
    position: absolute;
    width: 1px;
    height: 1px;
    padding: 0;
    margin: -1px;
    overflow: hidden;
    clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
    white-space: nowrap;
    border: 0;
  }
</style>
